python-textwrap3: textwrap3 is a compatibility back-port of Python 3.6’s textwrap
python-textwrap3: module that supports Python 2.6 forward. (Though honestly, if
python-textwrap3: you’re not already using at least 2.7, you’re way behind
python-textwrap3: the times!)  This makes a few new APIs such as shorten and the
python-textwrap3: max_lines parameter available in a compatible way to all Python
python-textwrap3: versions typically in current use.
